message.content:
1. The mean Systolic Blood Pressure (SBP) at minute 2 and minute 5 showed no significant difference between groups.
2. The mean Diastolic Blood Pressure (DBP) at minute 2, 5, and 15 showed no significant difference between groups.
3. The mean Heart Rate (HR) at all time points showed no significant difference between groups.
4. The mean Mean Arterial Pressure (MAP) at minute 2 and 15 showed no significant difference between groups.
5. The mean SBP at minute 10 and 15 in the hypertonic saline group was significantly higher than the normal group.
6. The mean DBP at minute 10 in the hypertonic saline group was significantly higher than the normal group.
7. The mean MAP at minute 5 and 10 in the hypertonic saline group was significantly higher than the normal group.
8. A P-value greater than 0.05 indicates no significant difference.
9. A P-value less than 0.05 indicates a significant difference.

messages.content:
Statement: The mean SBP at min 2 and min 5, mean of DBP at min 2, 5, and 15, mean of HR at all time points and mean of MAP at min 2 and 15 between groups were no significantly different (P > 0.05), but mean of SBP at min 10 and 15, mean of DBP at min 10, and mean of MAP at min 5 and 10 in hypertonic saline group was significantly more than the normal group (P < 0.05).
